==English==
===Alternative spellings===
May be hyphenated: '''sell-out'''
===Noun===
'''sellout''' (''plural'': '''[[sellouts]]''')
# an action in which principles are compromised for financial gain
# a person who compromises their principles for financial gain
#:''That rock star used to be hard core, but now he's just a '''sellout'''.''
# an event for which all tickets have been purchased
#:''The game was a '''sellout'''.''

===Verb===
'''sellout'''
# to do something for financial gain despite one's principles; to sacrifice one's principles for monetary advantage

